[{"id":41148,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math><mo>~</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>11</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mo>~</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mo>~</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mo>~</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>13</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"Average collision rate <math><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mo>-</mo></mover><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>&#960;</mi></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6.023</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>23</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>25</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>0.3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41163,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["1","3","2","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math><msub><mrow><mi>&#947;</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">mix</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">mix</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn></mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"italic\"></mi><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>mole</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (16 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41085,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Molecular specific heat at constant volume in&nbsp;terms of degrees of freedom&nbsp;is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math></p><p>Molecular specific heat of mixture at constant volume is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>mix</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#945;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41079,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Average Kinetic Energy per molecule&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>v</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math>.&nbsp;Therefore, we can conclude that the average kinetic energy of the molecules is directly proportional to the temperature of the gas and is independent of pressure, volume or the nature of the gas.</p><p>Hence, required ratio&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41095,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>From the ideal gas equation, total number of moles in the mixture are,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>25</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></math></p><p>If number of moles of oxygen are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and of&nbsp;hydrogen are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>&#8230;</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And total mass of the mixture</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mn>32</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>76</mn><mo>&#8230;</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Solving the above equations,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41172,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/image1-6ac42c6a-40e7-4f3d-9084-804829bbb352.jpg\" /><br /><br />Average linear velocity for collision to occur<br /><br /><math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />Change in momentum in 1 collision<br /><br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>u</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>∴</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi></math> average force in collision<br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />(<math><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo></math> root mean square speed)<br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>u</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>⇒</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>F</mi><mo>∝</mo><msup><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br /><math><mo>∴</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mo>∝</mo><mi>T</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>⇒</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>F</mi><mo>∝</mo><mi>T</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>⇒</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (10 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41070,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>551</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>651</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>451</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>751</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the rms speed of the argon molecules is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>The formula to calculate the rms speed of chlorine molecule is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Divide equation (1) by equation (2) and simplify to obtain the required ratio.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>Ar</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>Cl</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>Cl</mi></msub><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>Ar</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Substitute the values of the known parameters into equation (3) and solve to calculate the required value.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>Ar</mi></msub><mrow><mn>490</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><msqrt><mfrac><mn>71</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>71</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>490</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8776;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>651</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41036,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$P_{B}=P_{A}$","$P_{B}=P_{A} \\exp \\left(M \\omega^{2} l^{2} / 3 R T\\right)$","$P_{B}=P_{A} \\exp \\left(M \\omega^{2} l^{2} / R T\\right)$","$P_{B}=P_{A} \\exp \\left(M \\omega^{2} l^{2} / 2 R T\\right)$"],"answer":3,"solution":"<br>$A[(P + dP) - P] = (dm)(\\omega^2 x)$<br>$dP = \\dfrac{(dm)}{A} \\omega^2 x$<br>$dP = \\dfrac{(\\rho)(A)(dx)\\omega^2 x}{A}$<br>also $[PM = \\rho RT]$<br>$\\rho = \\dfrac{PM}{RT}$<br>$dP = \\left( \\dfrac{PM}{RT} \\right) \\omega^2 x \\, dx$<br>$\\int_{P_A}^{P_B} \\dfrac{dP}{P} = \\dfrac{\\omega^2 M}{RT} \\int_{0}^{\\ell} x \\, dx$<br>$\\ln \\left( \\dfrac{P_B}{P_A} \\right) = \\dfrac{\\omega^2 \\ell^2 M}{2RT}$<br>$P_B = P_A e^{\\dfrac{M\\omega^2 \\ell^2}{2RT}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41108,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The formula of root-mean-square speed in terms of absolute temperature and molecular mass of the gas&nbsp;is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mi>M</mi></msqrt></mfrac></math>, here we know that,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>M</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>M</mi><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41056,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>For mixture of gases, we can write</p><p> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41142,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2a735d06-540d-4df9-836a-4af6c74c27a7-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 149px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/72317618-59b5-49b8-b6b2-dae2aca77a62-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 175px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ca63f38e-fc46-43af-a1a3-63ef0e8658ed-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 175px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8e5f41c9-ecbb-4060-86bb-ea8d6e183d0f-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 149px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The average time taken&nbsp;by a moving particle between successive collisions or impacts is referred to as the mean free time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>&#964;</mi></mfenced></math>.</p><p>The average distance a moving particle travels between successive collisions or impacts is referred to as the mean free path <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>&#955;</mi></mfenced></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>P</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>So, the mean free time&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#964;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#955;</mi><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#964;</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mi>T</mi></msqrt></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41061,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>∞</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4c085d90-f6f0-4a5e-b68e-ff6a65779362.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 256px;\"/></p><p>For process <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>log</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>γ</mi><mi>log</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>V</mi><mi>γ</mi></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><msup><mi>V</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo></math> Constant</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>Likewise, for process <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>P</mi><msup><mi>V</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo></math> Constant</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>Also, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>R</mi><mo> </mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>By <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41181,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$3 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","$5 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","$6 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","$7 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Thermal energy corresponds to internal energy\nMass $=1 \\mathrm{~kg}$\ndensity $=8 \\mathrm{~kg} / \\mathrm{m}^3$\n$\\Rightarrow$ Volume $=\\frac{\\text { mass }}{\\text { density }}=\\frac{1}{8} \\mathrm{~m}^3$\nPressure $=8 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~N} / \\mathrm{m}^2$\n$\\therefore$ Internal Energy $=\\frac{5}{2} \\mathrm{P} \\times \\mathrm{V}=5 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2009","image":null},{"id":41122,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>88</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>28</mn><mn>28</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>44</mn><mn>44</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41133,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>87</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>83</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>119</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>38</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>As per given condition Half of kinetic energy is transferred into heat energy and raises the temperature of bullet</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>